Spain (AP) _ The Spanish government has ruled out any discussion of Basque independence in expected peace talks with the armed separatist group ETA.
In the Basque language, ETA stands for Basque Freedom and Homeland.
or Basque Homeland and Freedom, has been fighting since 1968 for an independent Basque state, leaving 800 people dead.
